Hello
I am 30 years old
I started cocaine at 20 years old.
I have never taken it every day, I wasn't super addicted
I used to take 1 or 2 times a month at most, but for about 6 months, maybe a year, I can't control myself when I drink alcohol.
Even though before I promised myself not to go looking for drugs, after 2 or 3 drinks I start to get hot and I tell myself "come on we only have one life, let's go" and it's impossible to control myself, I really want to take some.
So there you go, I know the problem is alcohol at the base but it's crazy impossible to stop, in family, with friends, for apero, etc.
Does anyone have this problem?
Thank you
stop drinking and the problem will be solved
One must sometimes force oneself to stop...
Have you at least talked to your family doctor about it?
Seeing an addict could do you some good, especially to "evaluate" your consumption
In fact, it's in the evening that it's harder to hold on mentally.
The day is going well
Hello,
I am politexic with a big problem of alcoholism
I have been alcohol-free for a few years, but I can't tell myself that I will never drink a drop of alcohol, even though I want to, not enough willpower maybe.
It happens to me that I relapse at times because it's stronger than me and as soon as I start, it's impossible for me to stop.
After that I sleep very badly and am sick the next day and especially I hate myself,
I am ashamed, of who I become when I drink and I suffer from it.
I can't drink normally
I drink all my glasses dry,
Why do I have this relationship with alcohol when a lot of people manage to drink normally??
I haven't drunk in 10 days.
This weekend I am invited to a birthday party and I am very very scared.
If you understand me live the same thing or have passed the cap I take all that can help me.
Thank you for reading and I await your responses.
amicably
