Hello to you Claude271. To start, I don't take LSD.
I think you should just see another doctor or a toxicologist (I don't know if that's the exact term)
If after 5 months you still experience this kind of "side effect" it's really bad.
So without wanting to panic you, you should go see a toxicologist who I think will prescribe you a treatment or emergency cache.
Otherwise, there are green numbers or specialized forums. Good luck. Peace
Hello Claude271,
For having gone through many times the state that you describe (following mixtures of chatter, microdots, TAZ, ketamine, finally everything that passed by there),
If I can give you one piece of advice, it's simply to tell you that all of this is just psychological.
Basically, the more you stress about these states, the worse they will get.
A very simple thing in these cases, you take deep breaths, you breathe gently, and you settle in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes sometimes you can have the impression that they are closing in on you).
After several months following a binge, especially when you mix substances, you can experience effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's only a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, seeing a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of those voices that are clogging up your head.
Keep up the good work, and stay positive.
Thank you to both of you for your answers
I will try to be patient.
